   {:e #blake3 "bb268f06294ba87dfbb24411d9a9db6afaaca6fb401d0dbe6a9effd29eecfb81" :a :harvest/accomplishments :v "Session entity: :recon/trace-15210e7b1dde6206; PEIRCE TRIADIC EPISTEMOLOGY MAPS TO UAQ: Deduction (exploitation) = I know X, therefore Y follows = low creativity, high confidence. Induction (exploration) = I have seen X in several places, therefore it is probably general = medium creativity, medium confidence. Abduction (creativity) = Y is surprising, if X were true Y would follow, therefore maybe X = high creativity, low confidence but high potential. The hypothesis ledger calibrates all three. The depth ladder tracks all three. The acquisition function ranks all three in a single queue.; COVERAGE MODEL AS MATERIALIZED VIEW: The coverage map (observations per region) should be a MaterializedView computed once per command, like StatusSnapshot. Project topology (file tree, package list from init/extractors) defines regions. Observation count per region is the coverage. The gap between topology size and coverage is the exploration gradient. This view enables generate_bridge_hypotheses to run in O(communities) instead of O(datoms). Already exists conceptually in store.views() — extend with coverage dimension.; Session entity: :recon/trace-19e4a3e80d9104cc; Session entity: :task/t-c76b7e9b; Session entity: :recon/trace-e0124b638ea93d11; Session entity: :recon/trace-e51c381befe390c5; Session entity: :recon/trace-b1e652f676e592b1; PROPOSAL GENERATION AT MULTIPLE SCALES: Local (comonadic neighborhood, tau near 0) = whats adjacent to what I know. Medium-range (semantic similarity, tau 0.5) = whats conceptually related across the store. Long-range (training data analogies, tau near 1.0) = what pattern from elsewhere might apply. Under the free energy formulation, tau EMERGES from the F(S) gradient landscape: when local observations are saturated (low projected delta-F(S) nearby), only distant bridges have high gradient, so the system naturally makes Levy-flight jumps. No separate creativity parameter needed.; Session entity: :recon/trace-b9bfd3ae5f07310a; FREE ENERGY COMPLEXITY TERM: F = surprise + complexity. Bridges are disproportionately valuable because they reduce BOTH terms simultaneously. Coverage fills reduce surprise but INCREASE complexity (more datoms). Bridges reduce surprise AND reduce complexity (fewer explanations needed). A bridge lets you REPLACE two separate explanations with one unified explanation = model COMPRESSION. The system should seek observations that COMPRESS understanding, not just expand it. This is literally the definition of INSIGHT: a single fact that reorganizes all other facts." :op :assert}
